# Theming System and CSS Variables

Boxel uses CSS custom properties (variables) for theming. When creating fields, use these variables with appropriate fallbacks that match your field's design system.

## Available Theme Variables

**Colors:** `--background`, `--foreground`, `--card`, `--card-foreground`, `--popover`, `--popover-foreground`, `--primary`, `--primary-foreground`, `--secondary`, `--secondary-foreground`, `--muted`, `--muted-foreground`, `--accent`, `--accent-foreground`, `--destructive`, `--destructive-foreground`, `--border`, `--input`, `--ring`

**Charts:** `--chart-1` through `--chart-5`

**Typography:** `--font-sans`, `--font-serif`, `--font-mono`

**Layout:** `--radius` (border radius), `--spacing` (base unit: 0.25rem)

**Shadows:** `--shadow-2xs`, `--shadow-xs`, `--shadow-sm`, `--shadow`, `--shadow-md`, `--shadow-lg`, `--shadow-xl`, `--shadow-2xl`

## Usage Pattern

**Always provide fallbacks matching your field's design:**

```gts
export class CustomField extends FieldDef {
  static edit = class Edit extends Component<typeof this> {
    <template>
      <input class="custom-input" type="text" />

      <style scoped>
        .custom-input {
          /* Theme variable with design-appropriate fallback */
          background: var(--input, #f5f5f5);
          color: var(--foreground, #1a1a1a);
          border: 1px solid var(--border, #e0e0e0);
          border-radius: var(--radius, 0.375rem);
          padding: calc(var(--spacing, 0.25rem) * 2);
          font-family: var(--font-sans, system-ui, sans-serif);
        }

        .custom-input:focus {
          outline: 2px solid var(--ring, #3b82f6);
          outline-offset: 2px;
        }

        .custom-input::placeholder {
          color: var(--muted-foreground, #9ca3af);
        }
      </style>
    </template>
  };
}
```

## State Examples

**Interactive states:**
```css
.button {
  background: var(--primary, #3b82f6);
  color: var(--primary-foreground, #ffffff);
}

.button:hover {
  background: var(--accent, #60a5fa);
  color: var(--accent-foreground, #1e293b);
}

.button:disabled {
  background: var(--muted, #f1f5f9);
  color: var(--muted-foreground, #94a3b8);
  opacity: 0.6;
}
```

**Error states:**
```css
.input-error {
  border-color: var(--destructive, #ef4444);
}

.error-message {
  color: var(--destructive, #ef4444);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
}
```

## Layout Patterns

**Spacing:**
```css
.container {
  padding: calc(var(--spacing) * 4);      /* 1rem */
  gap: calc(var(--spacing) * 2);           /* 0.5rem */
}
```

**Shadows:**
```css
.card {
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md, 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1));
}

.elevated {
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg, 0 10px 15px -3px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1));
}
```

**Charts:**
```css
.chart-bar:nth-child(1) { background: var(--chart-1, #3b82f6); }
.chart-bar:nth-child(2) { background: var(--chart-2, #10b981); }
.chart-bar:nth-child(3) { background: var(--chart-3, #f59e0b); }
```

## Complete Example

```gts
import { FieldDef, Component } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { action } from '@ember/object';

export class ThemedField extends FieldDef {
  static edit = class Edit extends Component<typeof this> {
    @tracked isOpen = false;

    <template>
      <div class="field-wrapper">
        <label>Select Option</label>
        <button class="trigger" {{on "click" (fn (mut this.isOpen) (not this.isOpen))}}>
          {{@model.value ?? "Choose..."}}
        </button>

        {{#if this.isOpen}}
          <div class="dropdown">
            {{#each @model.options as |option|}}
              <button class="option">{{option}}</button>
            {{/each}}
          </div>
        {{/if}}
      </div>

      <style scoped>
        .field-wrapper {
          display: flex;
          flex-direction: column;
          gap: calc(var(--spacing) * 2);
        }

        label {
          font-family: var(--font-sans, system-ui);
          font-weight: 600;
          font-size: 0.875rem;
          color: var(--foreground, #1a1a1a);
        }

        .trigger {
          background: var(--input, #f5f5f5);
          color: var(--foreground, #1a1a1a);
          border: 1px solid var(--border, #e0e0e0);
          border-radius: var(--radius, 0.375rem);
          padding: calc(var(--spacing) * 2);
          cursor: pointer;
        }

        .trigger:hover {
          background: var(--accent, #f0f9ff);
        }

        .trigger:focus {
          outline: 2px solid var(--ring, #3b82f6);
          outline-offset: 2px;
        }

        .dropdown {
          background: var(--popover, #ffffff);
          border: 1px solid var(--border, #e0e0e0);
          border-radius: var(--radius, 0.375rem);
          box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg, 0 10px 15px -3px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1));
          margin-top: calc(var(--spacing) * 2);
        }

        .option {
          width: 100%;
          padding: calc(var(--spacing) * 2);
          background: transparent;
          border: none;
          color: var(--popover-foreground, #1a1a1a);
          text-align: left;
          cursor: pointer;
        }

        .option:hover {
          background: var(--accent, #f0f9ff);
        }
      </style>
    </template>
  };
}
```

## Key Principles

1. **Always use `var(--variable, fallback)` syntax** - Never use variables without fallbacks
2. **Choose fallbacks that match your field's design** - Don't copy example values blindly
3. **Use semantic variable names** - `--primary`, not hard-coded colors
4. **Respect spacing system** - Use `calc(var(--spacing) * n)` for consistency
5. **Apply focus states** - Use `--ring` for accessibility
6. **Test without theme** - Ensure fallbacks create a cohesive design
